<br>
I was along for this one .... what happened was that the loot rules were posted where the raid was posted.  Problem was, when it came time to raid, a few people had backed out.  <br>
<br>
Brecht was seriously considering calling off the raid.  He stated as such.  What happened then is that a large portion of people apparently wanted to raid Vox badly enough that they started calling in friends and favors and we managed to get a last minute semi-workable situation set up.  <br>
<br>
That is something that no one seemed to notice or mention....Brecht was very nearly NOT going to raid...but he was asked to PLEASE continue.<br>
<br>
So, he went on about the normal course of things.  He was so busy trying to explain to the majority of the people there that had not been on a Vox raid (and several never on a dragon raid) what to do to keep folks alive so the loot rules weren't priority.  When we got into chat after several things already starting to go wrong...  <br>
<br>
    *** Yes, it was me that was killed in the buff hall when Vox aggroed there...so I'm pretty certain it wasn't a hallucination on Brecht's part***<br>
<br>
Brecht went over the basics and the specifics and then the loot rules.  As I remember it, as he said Okay....we are all here, any more questions...a few asked about the loot rules and Brecht even stated that we would sort out the &quot;special cirrcumstances&quot; after she was dead.  We logged back in and at least one group never got formed because there was a lot of shouting and ooc'ing over the loot rules....<br>
<br>
So, there ya go...I've even got the logs...was a pretty big night for this little bard and I'm glad I have something to remember it and all the really amazing people I met by.<br>
